// Content-Security-Policy, X-DNS-Prefetch-Control, and removes X-Powered-By.
```

#### 3. No Rate Limiting (OWASP A04 – Insecure Design)

Every endpoint is open to brute-force and denial-of-service attacks. A single attacker can hammer `/users` (or any future auth endpoint) indefinitely.

```js
// FIXED
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');

const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000,  // 15 minutes
  max: 100,                   // limit each IP to 100 requests per window
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
});

