No `cors` configuration is set, which means the browser's default same-origin policy is the only guard. If this API is ever called cross-origin (e.g., from a frontend), CORS must be explicitly configured — an open wildcard (`*`) would expose authenticated responses to any website.

```js
// FIXED – allow only your trusted frontend origin
